      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add your <strong>ground cumin </strong>with a couple of splashes of<strong> cold water</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 6-8 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>While the chicken is cooking, peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is cooked through, transfer to a clean board (reserve the pan) and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682597548155-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682597548155-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682597548155-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682597548155-x1000.jpg",
